b'Everyday superheroes don\xe2\x80\x99t all wear capes \xe2\x80\x93 sometimes they wear a red Costco badge!
A few weeks ago in Houston, Texas, John was checking out at the cash register at Costco. Getting distracted, he left behind his change: $194 to be exact.
Shortly after John returned home, he received a phone call. A young woman informed him that he left behind some cash. Thinking it may be a scam, John and his wife Barbara drove back to Costco together.
\xe2\x80\x9cHe didn\xe2\x80\x99t realize that he had forgotten the money,\xe2\x80\x9d Barbara said.
Kristina \xe2\x80\x93 a front end supervisor at the Galleria Costco \xe2\x80\x93 was waiting for them near the membership counter. Donning a badge, she held onto an envelope filled with $194.
Barbara and John thanked Kristina profusely, feeling appreciative that the employees who found the cash were so honest.
\xe2\x80\x9cIn these stressful times, we have been so very impressed with Kristina and all employees at this Costco, from the excellent staff at the pharmacy to the greeters, cashiers, and stockers,\xe2\x80\x9d Barbara said. \xe2\x80\x9cMost of the pharmacy employees and greeters know us by name. Now, we are delighted to add Kristina to our friend list,\xe2\x80\x9d she said.
How are you spreading kindness? Share your Costco stories with us in the comments below, or use #CostcoKindness. Your name and answer may be featured.'
